A developer is tasked with creating necessary configurations for AWS CloudFormation that is extensively used in a project. After declaring the necessary stack policy, the developer realized that the users still do not have access to stack resources. The stack policy created by the developer looks like so:

{"Statement":[{"Effect":"Allow","Action":"Update:*","Principal":"*","Resource":"*"},{"Effect":"Deny","Action":"Update:*","Principal":"*","Resource":"LogicalResourceId/ProductionDatabase"}]}

Why are the users unable to access the stack resources even after giving access permissions to all?
